16
00:02:27,434 --> 00:02:29,658
I've no idea. I don't get it at all.

17
00:02:29,809 --> 00:02:32,236
It's the logo for the SOS Brigade.

18
00:02:32,487 --> 00:02:37,280
A logo? That's funny, 'cause to me, it looks
more like a drunken tapeworm wrapped around a tube.

19
00:02:37,305 --> 00:02:39,010
Well, take a closer look at it!

20
00:02:39,241 --> 00:02:42,567
See, it says "SOS Brigade" right there in the middle!

21
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:47,971
<i>Now that she pointed it out, I can't really
say for sure whether I can or can't see it,</i>

22
00:02:48,189 --> 00:02:50,852
<i>but I wouldn't disagree with
anybody if they said it was or wasn't.</i>

23
00:02:51,217 --> 00:02:53,776
<i>And how many negatives did I just use in that sentence?</i>

24
00:02:53,909 --> 00:02:55,917
<i>If somebody's got time, total it up for me.</i>

25
00:02:56,119 --> 00:02:58,218
You're the one that's got the most free time.

26
00:02:58,814 --> 00:03:02,993
Anyway, I was thinking of putting this thing
on the homepage of the SOS Brigade website.

27
00:03:03,082 --> 00:03:05,733
<i>You mean, this pathetic website that only has a homepage?</i>

28
00:03:05,854 --> 00:03:09,141
This website that you made isn't
getting us any visitors at all.

29
00:03:09,265 --> 00:03:10,712
It's so frustrating.

30
00:03:10,813 --> 00:03:12,908
